label.intro:
Interpret your findings to make sense of your analyses.


The research study is not complete until the data is interpreted with relation to the research questions. In a good research study, the interpretation will provide insights that could not have been predicted initially. The best research often raises more questions than it answers.

What useful information can the data tell us about the agricultural research skills and experience of the students on this course? Does this information suggest ways that we should adapt the course to meet the needs of this particular set of students?
